It's a good start but missing a few important things for your specific project. Here's a more complete version:
gitignore# Python-generated files
__pycache__/
*.py[oc]
build/
dist/
wheels/
*.egg-info

# Virtual environments
.venv
venv/
env/

# Environment variables
.env
.env.local

# Data files - too large for GitHub
data/
*.csv
*.jsonl
*.json

# Trained models - too large for GitHub
models/
*.joblib
*.pt
*.pkl

# Outputs
outputs/

*.pth